            <scopecontent id="aspace_1967580c068492e62b5c388319b1b4d0">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Elisha Bradley Family Papers fill one box and consist of one letter, deeds, and an account book. The letter was written by S. Hart, Jr., to Harriet Canfield, later wife of Anson Bradley. The two men chiefly represented in the deeds are Elisha Bradley of Southbury and Anson Bradley of the same town. Folder 3 contains an 1805-1806 account book of Elisha Bradley's woolen business.</p>
            </scopecontent>
